<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="25" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="25">Distribution and biotope.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="25">
From the Barents Sea south to Algarve (Portugal), the Mediterranean Sea, Azores, Madeira, Canary Islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas, P" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Mededelingen" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" pagination="89 - 98" title="Chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) procured by the CANCAP I-VII expeditions, 1976 - 86." volume="65" year="1991">Kaas 1991</bibRefCitation>
), near Iceland, Faroes Islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Sneli, J-A" journalOrPublisher="Annales Societatis Scientiarum Faeroensis Suplemment" pageId="12" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 190" title="The Marine Mollusca of the Faroes." volume="42" year="2005">Sneli et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
), Greenland and the east coast of North America (
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas, P" journalOrPublisher="EJ Brill / W Backhuys Eds., Leiden" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" title="Monograph of living chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora), Vol. 1: Order Neoloricata: Lepidopleurina." year="1985 a">Kaas and Van Belle 1985a</bibRefCitation>
). It lives from 15 to 555 meters depth (
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas, P" journalOrPublisher="EJ Brill / W Backhuys Eds., Leiden" pageId="11" pageNumber="34" title="Monograph of living chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora), Vol. 1: Order Neoloricata: Lepidopleurina." year="1985 a">Kaas and Van Belle 1985a</bibRefCitation>
). Usually found feeding on coralline algae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
